00:25:00,319 --> 00:25:02,776
I know what you have in common!

524
00:25:03,216 --> 00:25:06,592
You’re both hotheaded!

525
00:25:07,114 --> 00:25:07,847
Let me go first!

526
00:25:07,895 --> 00:25:10,263
- No, I’ll go!
- I-’ll go! I will!

527
00:25:10,288 --> 00:25:12,818
- Wait a minute, I’ll go first!
- Me! I said it first!

528
00:25:14,756 --> 00:25:17,401
You know, you shouldn’t
have treated your son like that.

529
00:25:17,543 --> 00:25:19,271
At first, I was just asking.

530
00:25:19,586 --> 00:25:22,115
I just wanted to ask if
he was really my child.

531
00:25:24,647 --> 00:25:27,193
But I should’ve asked you instead.

532
00:25:28,357 --> 00:25:31,826
Dixie, what’s your real intention here?

533
00:25:33,281 --> 00:25:34,281
Intention?

534
00:25:35,115 --> 00:25:37,607
You’re asking me what my intention is?

535
00:25:38,411 --> 00:25:40,046
You know, if I had an ulterior motive,

536
00:25:40,071 --> 00:25:42,779
I would’ve looked for
you when I was pregnant!

537
00:25:44,142 --> 00:25:48,088
You know what, I’m an independent woman,

538
00:25:48,113 --> 00:25:52,380
and I don’t want to impose myself
on someone who doesn’t want me.

539
00:25:53,089 --> 00:25:55,927
Especially on someone
who can’t move on from

540
00:25:56,002 --> 00:25:58,617
“the one” who chose
his best friend over him!

541
00:25:58,642 --> 00:26:00,840
Shh! Hey, stop it! That’s not true!

542
00:26:00,865 --> 00:26:03,711
Oh, whatever! Whatever!

543
00:26:03,822 --> 00:26:05,505
All I wanted was

544
00:26:05,730 --> 00:26:11,748
to give our child a chance to get to
know you before we migrate to the US.

545
00:26:13,024 --> 00:26:14,569
You’re moving to the US?

546
00:26:15,025 --> 00:26:18,178
Yes, so please,

547
00:26:18,770 --> 00:26:21,006
can you make things
right with your son?

548
00:26:25,314 --> 00:26:26,314
What?

549
00:26:27,100 --> 00:26:28,581
Ford’s leaving?

550
00:26:29,094 --> 00:26:32,952
What about us?

551
00:26:33,497 --> 00:26:34,692
For the memories!

552
00:26:36,156 --> 00:26:39,202
- BRB, I’m going to cry –
- Psst!

553
00:26:39,255 --> 00:26:43,014
You’re being so dramatic.
Go inside! Go, go!

554
00:26:47,169 --> 00:26:48,498
Look at Tash, see?

555
00:26:48,875 --> 00:26:53,998
Just one glance and she’s
head over heels for Ford!

556
00:26:54,449 --> 00:26:58,483
Meanwhile, his father doesn’t
even feel a spark of connection.

557
00:26:59,991 --> 00:27:02,107
I do feel something, BFF.

558
00:27:02,133 --> 00:27:03,133
It’s just…

559
00:27:03,969 --> 00:27:08,819
sorry, sorry, if I seem so reluctant
to get close to my own son.

560
00:27:09,495 --> 00:27:11,014
Honestly, why should I?

561
00:27:11,561 --> 00:27:13,287
They’re just going to leave me too.

562
00:27:14,265 --> 00:27:16,889
Then again, everyone leaves me eventually.

563
00:27:19,016 --> 00:27:20,334
You know, BFF,

564
00:27:20,516 --> 00:27:23,366
having a family is different.

565
00:27:23,391 --> 00:27:27,959
Even for just a moment, let
your son feel that he has a father.

566
00:27:30,332 --> 00:27:33,537
I guess you have a point.

567
00:27:35,057 --> 00:27:37,621
And about this whole “everyone
leaves” thing – no one’s leaving you.

568
00:27:37,645 --> 00:27:39,084
Who would? Us?

569
00:27:39,517 --> 00:27:43,366
We’re here for you, through thick and thin.

570
00:27:43,785 --> 00:27:45,347
You just don’t believe it.

571
00:27:47,221 --> 00:27:48,973
See? Look at us!

572
00:27:48,998 --> 00:27:50,869
- Exactly!
- See?

573
00:27:52,015 --> 00:27:53,015
Sho K!

574
00:27:53,040 --> 00:27:54,435
Sho K!

575
00:27:54,719 --> 00:27:57,194
Sorry, sorry, sorry!

576
00:27:57,529 --> 00:27:58,779
She’s not into you.

577
00:27:58,804 --> 00:28:01,042
Sorry, you’ll be left
here in the Philippines.

578
00:28:01,067 --> 00:28:03,973
I’m the one she’s taking to the US of A.

579
00:28:04,003 --> 00:28:04,576
Hey.

580
00:28:04,601 --> 00:28:05,673
That’s Entertainment!

581
00:28:05,703 --> 00:28:06,860
Why do you look like that?

582
00:28:06,885 --> 00:28:08,271
This is what Dixie wants!

583
00:28:08,309 --> 00:28:10,050
- So she’ll fall for me.
- What Dixie?

584
00:28:10,075 --> 00:28:11,772
You’re just after her money.

585
00:28:11,885 --> 00:28:13,071
No, bro.

586
00:28:13,778 --> 00:28:16,310
By this time,
I’ve genuinely fallen for her.

587
00:28:16,335 --> 00:28:17,344
- What?!
- Yes.

588
00:28:17,526 --> 00:28:19,350
Because I like this kind of thing.

589
00:28:20,772 --> 00:28:27,959
Young-looking but already super
old, really aged, almost ancient.

590
00:28:29,360 --> 00:28:30,460
Wow, that’s harsh!

591
00:28:36,993 --> 00:28:38,169
Good thing I dodged that one.

592
00:28:38,946 --> 00:28:40,761
She almost hit me!

593
00:28:43,705 --> 00:28:45,616
Why did you call me here?

594
00:28:48,540 --> 00:28:51,881
I heard from your mom
that you’re migrating soon.

595
00:28:53,465 --> 00:28:54,465
Yeah, and so?

596
00:28:55,954 --> 00:29:01,506
I just wanted to make it up to you,
even a little, before that happens, son.

597
00:29:10,121 --> 00:29:11,121
How?

598
00:29:13,208 --> 00:29:15,944
I missed so many of your birthdays.

599
00:29:16,584 --> 00:29:19,508
I wanted us to celebrate them.

600
00:29:20,261 --> 00:29:23,051
But I’ll fast-forward everything, okay?

601
00:29:23,130 --> 00:29:25,053
If that’s alright with you.

602
00:29:27,357 --> 00:29:28,357
Of course!

603
00:29:31,506 --> 00:29:34,246
Here, son, I had this made.

604
00:29:34,271 --> 00:29:37,295
The cake is coming next!

605
00:29:38,016 --> 00:29:40,582
Just to celebrate your birthdays.

606
00:29:40,607 --> 00:29:41,607
Thanks, Mom!

607
00:29:45,093 --> 00:29:46,874
Happy birthday, cousin!

608
00:29:46,899 --> 00:29:48,546
Happy birthday!

609
00:29:48,571 --> 00:29:49,571
Thank you!

610
00:29:50,827 --> 00:29:52,203
Okay, wait. Group photo, group photo first!

611
00:29:52,227 --> 00:29:52,779
There we go.

612
00:29:52,804 --> 00:29:54,045
Alright, ready?

613
00:29:54,362 --> 00:29:58,919
Three, two, one, smile! So cute!

614
00:30:02,178 --> 00:30:04,249
- With her too.
- So cute, it’s perfect!

615
00:30:09,396 --> 00:30:11,048
- Happy birthday!
- Aww, thank you!

616
00:30:12,094 --> 00:30:12,737
What’s this?

617
00:30:12,893 --> 00:30:14,139
Here, cousin!

618
00:30:14,164 --> 00:30:15,783
This one, wait!

619
00:30:18,940 --> 00:30:21,085
- Happy birthday!
- Thank you!

620
00:30:22,606 --> 00:30:23,636
It’s so nice!

621
00:30:25,772 --> 00:30:27,030
Thanks again!

622
00:30:27,966 --> 00:30:28,966
Oh, wow!

623
00:30:29,584 --> 00:30:31,890
Open it, open it! There’s something inside.

624
00:30:36,498 --> 00:30:37,612
It’s beautiful!

625
00:30:38,204 --> 00:30:39,423
Wow!

626
00:30:39,702 --> 00:30:40,673
Brand new!

627
00:30:40,698 --> 00:30:42,154
Brand new?

628
00:30:46,241 --> 00:30:47,241
Brand new!

629
00:30:48,166 --> 00:30:49,542
Whoa!

630
00:30:52,576 --> 00:30:54,019
Vintage!

631
00:30:54,762 --> 00:30:56,074
Vintage!

632
00:30:56,099 --> 00:30:57,333
Happy birthday!

633
00:31:00,368 --> 00:31:01,964
- Wow!
- Wow!

634
00:31:03,659 --> 00:31:04,878
Wow, a suit!

635
00:31:05,470 --> 00:31:05,970
Does it fit?

636
00:31:05,995 --> 00:31:06,995
Perfect fit!

637
00:31:11,426 --> 00:31:12,426
Just like that.

638
00:31:13,229 --> 00:31:14,767
Let’s not drag this out any longer.

639
00:31:16,079 --> 00:31:23,064
Well, I guess it’s time
to say goodbye, Karl!

640
00:31:24,936 --> 00:31:25,936
Bye, Dixie!

641
00:31:26,549 --> 00:31:28,659
I’ll just visit you when I can.

642
00:31:30,773 --> 00:31:31,773
Whatever!

643
00:31:32,247 --> 00:31:34,771
Whatever happens, just remember,

644
00:31:36,638 --> 00:31:38,328
we’ll always have tonight!

645
00:31:42,230 --> 00:31:43,230
Don’t!

646
00:31:44,345 --> 00:31:47,121
If I give in, I might not be able to leave.

647
00:31:49,865 --> 00:31:50,894
What time is it?

648
00:31:50,928 --> 00:31:53,228
We might be late for the flight! Let’s go!

649
00:31:53,253 --> 00:31:55,625
- Oh, right!
- We’re going to be late. Let’s go!

650
00:31:56,284 --> 00:31:58,808
Hide that smile of yours.
You’re way too happy!

651
00:32:00,740 --> 00:32:04,185
Ah, Ford, take care, okay?

652
00:32:05,491 --> 00:32:06,934
Look after your mom.

653
00:32:09,575 --> 00:32:10,575
Yes, Dad.

654
00:32:11,335 --> 00:32:12,335
Thank you, Dad!

655
00:32:14,957 --> 00:32:15,957
Son.

656
00:32:19,651 --> 00:32:20,789
Oh, Ford!

657
00:32:20,814 --> 00:32:21,240
Yes?

658
00:32:21,811 --> 00:32:25,748
I printed out some of our photos.
For the memories.

659
00:32:27,794 --> 00:32:28,794
Bye.

660
00:32:29,905 --> 00:32:30,919
Thanks, Tash!

661
00:32:31,696 --> 00:32:33,162
I’m so glad I got to know you.

662
00:32:34,431 --> 00:32:35,824
Let’s chat sometime?

663
00:32:35,967 --> 00:32:36,967
Sure.

664
00:32:36,996 --> 00:32:38,271
Take care, okay?

665
00:32:40,838 --> 00:32:44,865
Tash, take care of
yourself, alright? Come here!

666
00:32:45,056 --> 00:32:47,210
Wow, you’re so
emotional, like you’re family!

667
00:32:47,235 --> 00:32:48,412
Exactly!

668
00:32:48,437 --> 00:32:49,437
Bye, cousin!

669
00:32:49,533 --> 00:32:50,893
- Bye, cousin.
- Safe flight, okay?

670
00:32:51,139 --> 00:32:52,139
Take care.

671
00:32:52,632 --> 00:32:53,833
Am I included?

672
00:32:54,399 --> 00:32:55,399
Bro, take care, man.

673
00:32:55,691 --> 00:32:56,572
Safe flight.

674
00:32:56,597 --> 00:32:58,037
- Take care!
- Take care!

675
00:32:58,259 --> 00:32:59,259
Take care.

676
00:33:00,399 --> 00:33:01,399
- Be safe.
- Take care!

677
00:33:01,715 --> 00:33:04,958
Well, well, well! Yes, yes, yes!

678
00:33:07,131 --> 00:33:11,238
I just came from DOH
and I got my passport!

679
00:33:11,279 --> 00:33:12,369
- DOH?!
- DOH?!

680
00:33:12,403 --> 00:33:13,361
- DOH?!
- DOH?!

681
00:33:13,386 --> 00:33:14,152
Yes!

682
00:33:14,177 --> 00:33:17,847
I also bought a parachute just in
case of emergency, I can save myself!

683
00:33:18,073 --> 00:33:20,972
And now, I’m standing
in front of the girl

684
00:33:21,126 --> 00:33:24,035
taking me to the US. Hi!

685
00:33:25,283 --> 00:33:26,640
Smells awful again!

686
00:33:26,665 --> 00:33:29,378
- Wait a minute, you have a passport.
- Yes.

687
00:33:31,256 --> 00:33:32,839
But you don’t have a visa!

688
00:33:33,097 --> 00:33:36,119
And what’s your name again? I forgot.

689
00:33:36,144 --> 00:33:37,763
- Iskineport.
- Iskineport.

690
00:33:37,788 --> 00:33:38,368
Iskineport.

691
00:33:38,393 --> 00:33:42,608
Ah! Hey! I’m leaving! I almost forgot!

692
00:33:42,633 --> 00:33:44,415
He’s leaving! He’s leaving!

693
00:33:44,440 --> 00:33:46,332
- Okay, let’s go! Bye, my love!
- Bye!

694
00:33:46,357 --> 00:33:47,708
- Bye!
- Bye-bye!

695
00:33:47,733 --> 00:33:50,108
- Bye! Take care!
- Bye, take care!

696
00:33:50,133 --> 00:33:51,471
- Bye, take care!
- Bye-bye!

697
00:33:51,944 --> 00:33:54,511
She left on his own, huh?

698
00:33:54,834 --> 00:33:56,606
She really didn’t
take me with her.

699
00:33:56,631 --> 00:34:00,298
Dixie! I thought you were
taking me to Washington, Dixie?

700
00:34:00,323 --> 00:34:01,603
Did you see what I said?

701
00:34:02,656 --> 00:34:03,656
Hmm?

702
00:34:03,844 --> 00:34:07,405
You keep stealing the spotlight, but
they don’t even remember your name!

703
00:34:08,186 --> 00:34:09,610
I’m not good at courting.

704
00:34:09,635 --> 00:34:11,075
You’re the one who’s
good with women.

705
00:34:12,158 --> 00:34:14,151
Let’s stop talking about that.

706
00:34:14,236 --> 00:34:14,864
Huh?

707
00:34:14,889 --> 00:34:16,472
What you’re saying isn’t right.

708
00:34:16,497 --> 00:34:18,230
Sshh, just stay quiet!

709
00:34:18,340 --> 00:34:18,730
Okay!

710
00:34:18,755 --> 00:34:19,943
- Don’t say anything anymore.
- It’s been a long...

711
00:34:19,967 --> 00:34:22,984
- Don’t say anything! Sshh!
- It’s been a long...

712
00:34:23,251 --> 00:34:24,220
Come here!

713
00:34:24,245 --> 00:34:26,297
Bye now, we’re
going to the market!

714
00:34:26,322 --> 00:34:27,698
It’s been a long time...

715
00:34:30,575 --> 00:34:35,209
Yeah! You know what, I failed last time.

716
00:34:35,234 --> 00:34:36,025
Yeah.

717
00:34:36,050 --> 00:34:42,058
But this time, I can’t fail,
because try and try until you…

718
00:34:42,083 --> 00:34:43,222
- Fail.
- Fail.

719
00:34:45,383 --> 00:34:48,370
- That’s the new beginnings.
- That’s the new beginnings.

720
00:34:49,587 --> 00:34:50,101
Hey!

721
00:34:50,126 --> 00:34:51,406
- BFF!
- BFF!

722
00:34:51,444 --> 00:34:53,831
- Here, here, here! It’s Dixie!
- I like this!

723
00:34:54,722 --> 00:34:58,408
Oh, it’s you! I thought
Attorney Topacio walked in!

724
00:35:00,473 --> 00:35:04,035
You’re something else!
There you go again, BFF!

725
00:35:04,060 --> 00:35:04,967
It’s you!

726
00:35:04,992 --> 00:35:06,976
There you go again,
with that laugh of yours!

727
00:35:07,001 --> 00:35:08,952
Wait, wait, Dixie’s waiting!

728
00:35:08,977 --> 00:35:09,779
Oh, hello!

729
00:35:09,822 --> 00:35:13,002
She said sorry she couldn’t
make it. They couldn’t make it. But…

730
00:35:13,027 --> 00:35:13,455
Who’s that?

731
00:35:13,480 --> 00:35:14,250
It’s Dixie!

732
00:35:14,275 --> 00:35:15,661
There she is, watching!

733
00:35:15,705 --> 00:35:17,612
She seems like she can’t hear well,

734
00:35:17,763 --> 00:35:21,887
but she said congratulations
on the relaunch of your bakery.

735
00:35:22,053 --> 00:35:24,526
Wow! Hi, Dixie!

736
00:35:25,276 --> 00:35:27,456
- Hi, Dixie! Hi, Ford!
- I miss you!

737
00:35:27,492 --> 00:35:32,374
Well, it’s good, Karl, that you’re
still in touch with Dixie and Ford!

738
00:35:32,399 --> 00:35:35,245
Of course! I learned
that from you guys!

739
00:35:35,270 --> 00:35:37,813
You said, family first!

740
00:35:37,838 --> 00:35:41,181
Oh, right, didn’t you teach me…

741
00:35:41,788 --> 00:35:49,978
In struggles and joy, Pers
is the first, Pers is the hero!
